===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|reyn}}, {{m|enm|rein}}, from {{inh|en|ang|reġn}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*regn}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*regną}} (compare {{cog|fy|rein}}, {{cog|nl|regen}}, {{cog|de|Regen}}, {{cog|da|-}} and {{cog|no|regn}}), of uncertain origin. Possibly from {{w|pre-Germanic}} {{m|ine-pro|*Hréǵ-no}}-, from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*Hreǵ-||to flow}} (compare {{cog|la|rigō||wet, soak}}, {{cog|lt|rõki||drizzling rain}}, {{cog|sq|rrjedh||to flow, drip}}), although the consonant reflexes don't match.

